programme.desc: Liam Toland and Rosie Foley face an uphill struggle as they try to encourage their charges to commit to their training programme. programme.desc: Stephen and outfitting partner, Brad Peacock, are in Mexico hoping to fill a once-in-a-lifetime Sheldony mule deer tag on Tiburon Island(n)

programme.title: Winchester Deadly Passion
programme.desc: When it comes to spring turkey hunting, Illinois is at the top of Melissa's list for non-stop gobbler action. Melissa's hunting with Golden Triangle Whitetail with both her bow and shotgun(n)

programme.title: Hardcore Pursuit
programme.desc: Travel north with Mike P and Ryan as they head up to Saskatchewan to battle the bone-chilling elements of hunting the rut with Lucky Man Outfitters. There are lots of big bucks, you've just got to be patient and hope one shows up(n)

programme.title: Full Draw Adventures
programme.desc: Jamie Hayes and a friend travel to western Kansas where they intend to unleash an arrow on a few Midwestern brutes. As they hunt some of the finest country for whitetails, each encounter brings them closer to that pivotal moment(n)

programme.title: Team Fitzgerald Vintage Country Lifestyle
programme.desc: Part 2. Guy shares helpful information on using scents with food plots for success. Dan bow shoots a hoss buck with his trusty Mathews(n)

programme.title: Major League Bowhunter
programme.desc: Part 2. Duff heads up to southeastern Montana to hunt river bottom whitetails. With his new strategy of hunting these big bucks from the ground, Duff takes aim a mature buck. On Halloween, Duff comes to full draw on a great Montana buck(n)

programme.title: Bowhunter TV
programme.desc: Curt Wells heads back to the Colorado high country with outfitting friend Doyle Worbington in search of his all-time favorite animal to hunt: the rutting bull elk(n)

programme.title: Trained Assassins
programme.desc: Part 1. The crew is back chasing rack bucks on their own home turf in Mississippi and Louisiana. They have waited long enough, and now it's time to start laying down some of these southern brutes(n)

programme.title: In-Fisherman
programme.desc: The staff fine tunes tactics for guaranteed success on the water as they use tube tricks for largemouth bass, travel to one of North America's great muskie fisheries and spider rig world-class water for giant crappies(n)

programme.title: Reel Time With Florida Sportsman
programme.desc: Captain George Gozdz fishes with marine painter, Yusniel Snatos, in Sarasota, Fla(n)

programme.title: North American Whitetail Television
programme.desc: Stan Potts bowhunts Illinois and doubles down in Montana with his rifle; Dr. Deer considers whether missing a buck will ruin a hunting spot; and we'll talk real-world archery practice(n)

programme.title: Whitetail Fix
programme.desc: Part 3. It's late November and the rut is still in full swing. Mike Marsteller heads to the Weldon compound to try his hand at one of those big bucks that Chuck and Matt have had so much success with(n)

programme.title: Whitetail Explorer
programme.desc: Stan has a new favorite decoy spot, and his son, Terry Potts, is after a 200" Illinois buck he has history with called Rockyford. Terry has numerous sightings and found both sheds the previous year which measured 198"(n)

programme.title: Dominant Bucks
programme.desc: Learn the Dominant Buck tactics of North Carolina hunter Roy Smith. Join Roy as he demonstrates his do-it-yourself approach to successful capturing of a buck hunt on film(n)

programme.title: Respect the Game TV
programme.desc: Larry McCoy joins Philip Vanderpool at Powder River Outfitters to hunt Montana whitetails(n)

programme.title: Big Deer TV
programme.desc: On the heels of a highly successful deer camp in Oklahoma, Mike rolls solo across America's Heartland to the big buck haven of southeastern Kansas. Assisted by 180 outfitters, Mike must rely on his own instincts and experience on a self-guided hunt(n)

programme.title: GunVenture
programme.desc: Ryan heads to the Gulf Coast to go on a monster hunt: shark fishing during the day and hog hunting at night. Along the way, he grabs an aerial view of the Florida coast, catches a really big ray and braves treacherous bridges looking for pigs(n)

programme.title: Guns & Gear
programme.desc: Smith & Wesson introduces new M&P15 rifles. Also: Colt ammo from DoubleTap; SIG's P320 air pistol; the full-featured 10 and 10S from Stag Arms; the Calvin Elite 2-Stage Rem 700 trigger from Timney; and concealed carry options from Springfield Armory(n)

programme.title: Jon Baker's Guide 4 Adventure
programme.desc: Jon Baker and Keith Hilty cruise the river for caribou in the hills of Alaska's vast wilderness(n)

programme.title: Beyond The Divide
programme.sub-title: Brown Quail on Vansittart Island Tasmania
programme.desc: Rob and his eight-year-old German shorthaired pointer, Angus, travel to Bass Strait to stay with Chris Rhodes of Rockjaw Tours. For three days, they hunt the rolling tussock of the Vansittart Island for a unique and abundant population of brown quail(n)

programme.title: Trailing the Hunter's Moon
programme.desc: Larry is after a buck that gave him the slip a couple of years earlier, a big typical 12-point(n)

programme.title: Trijicon's World of Sports Afield
programme.sub-title: Mongolia - A Quest for Argali Pt. 2
programme.desc: Part 2. Dan Catlin continues his expedition into wild Mongolia. From the high desert to the famed Altai Mountains, Dan and Miguel Madero pursue the legendary altai argali as well as maral stags that call the wind swept wilderness of Mongolia home(n)

programme.title: Hornady's Dark & Dangerous
programme.desc: Dave Fulson experiences the unique hunt for duiker in the thick forest of CAR. Calvin Smith tries to close the deal with Mr. Spots, and Neil Emory continues his search for cape buffalo in the Nuanetsi conservancy(n)

programme.title: Petersen's Hunting Adventures
programme.desc: Kevin Steele and Tony Miele travel to the Texas Hill Country for a pre-Christmas hunt for fallow deer along with James Jeffrey from Lost Horizon Outfitters(n)

programme.title: Savage Outdoors
programme.desc: There is only one place the crew would want to be during the week of Halloween and that is at the Grigsby Farm in Illinois. Mike Stroff goes to his favorite stand on the farm for his first afternoon sit and one of the shooters on their hit list shows up(n)

programme.title: Buckventures' The Woodsman
programme.desc: The team hunts with several youth hunters, including Daniel McVay taking his son Greyson on his first hunt ever(n)

programme.title: Huntin' the Backwoods
programme.desc: Part 1. Karl returns to South Africa to hunt with Koringkoppie Safaris, and brings Troy Lauffer along for his first trip to Africa. It doesn't take long for Troy to get accustomed to hunting in Africa. Karl comes face to face with the Grey Ghost(n)

programme.title: Out-There TV
programme.desc: Corey gets a call that will change his outlook on life. Corey joins forces with Moment of Peace Adventures to take Ayden on a whitetail and hog hunt(n)
